PyMT - Examples
===============

About
-----

All examples are made to show you how powerfull PyMT are.

If you want to play fast, just run (it will launch desktop app.) :

  python launcher.py

List of examples
----------------

  * 3Ddrawing   - draw on a cow !
  * 3Dviewer	- rotate the head of a 3d monkey
  * bloop		- game with sound, simple and great !
  * bubblebattle - game to fight against bubble
  * bubblebomb  - another game with bubble
  * camera      - show camera inside a scatter
  * desktop		- launch some example in inner window, rotate and move them !
  * flowchart	- construct flow chart in multitouch !
  * frigdeletter - letter on fridge
  * gestures	- a base to detect gesture
  * inneranimation - example how to use inner animation
  * kaswy       - example from kaswy
  * mandelbrot  - show a mandelbrot fratal with glsl
  * paint		- paint on the wall
  * particles	- magical particles are showed under each touch
  * pictures	- pictures on wall, move, rotate...
  * pyzzle		- a video pyzzle (avbin needed)
  * sandbox     - lot of example not working yet
  * scoller		- example to scroll icon + shadow
  * sinemixer	- using ounk+csound, modify sound with slider !
  * stylus		- stylus exampel with dell xt2
  * svg			- svg pictures showed in scatter widget
  * tictactoe	- tictactoe game
  * touchtracer - trace each touch path
  * untangle	- game with circle / line, try to untangle them :)
  * videoplayer - play video under pymt
  * vkeyboard	- demonstration of vkeyboard widget
  * wang		- a mt pong !
  * widgets		- lot examples of widgets
  * xmlgui		- demonstration of xml widget

If you want to test example, you can :

  cd examples/untangle
  python untangle.py


PyMT Usage
----------

Some options are available in all pymt applications :

  -h, --help                        prints this mesage
  -f, --fullscreen                  force run in fullscreen
  -w, --windowed                    force run in window
  -p, --port=x                      specify TUIO port (default 3333)
  -H, --host=xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx        specify TUIO host (default 127.0.0.1)
  -F, --fps                         show fps in window

